##
## Protocol for tree conversion.
##

##
## Exported Definitions
##

## `tree.indent(level, maxColumns)`: Converts the tree to a string, indented
## at the given `level`, and aiming to use no more than `maxColumns`
## characters in a single line.
export fn .indent(level, maxColumns);

## `tree.flatten()`: Converts the tree to an un-indented string.
export fn .flatten();

## `tree.prefersFlat()`: Returns `tree` if it "likes" to be flattened, or
## void if not.
export fn. prefersFlat();
